Story: The Honest Boy

One day, a boy was walking in the market.
He saw a wallet on the road.

The boy picked up the wallet.
There was a lot of money inside it.

The boy thought, “This is not my money.”
He went to the police station.

He gave the wallet to the police officer.
After some time, the owner came there.

The owner was very happy.
He thanked the boy for his honesty.

The police officer also praised the boy.
The boy felt proud because he did the right thing.

Moral: Honesty is the best policy.

Practice Questions (for speaking)

Where was the boy walking?

What did he find on the road?

Where did he take the wallet?

How did the owner feel?

What is the moral of the story?
